Converting JSON to JavaScript Object


Mostly we fetch JSON from HTTP response or from a file,but we can store the JSON as string
and we can change to Object for sake of demonstrartion. In JavaScript the keyword JSON
has parse() and stringify() methods.

When we want to change the JSON to an object we parse the JSON using JSON.parse()
When we want to change the object to an JSON we use JSON.stringify()
